subject: College Athletics
Swimming
lead_paragraph: Lacey Nymeyer won the 100 freestyle to help Arizona earn its first national title at the N.C.A.A. Women’s Division I Swimming and Diving Championships. The Wildcats used five relay titles and two individual champions over the three-day event in Columbus, Ohio, to amass 484 points.
